The paper discusses quantum finite automata, which are a topic in theoretical computer science and fall under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper specifically focuses on hybrid models of QFA, which involve both quantum and classical states, and this topic is closely related to quantum computing (cs.QL) and quantum information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses language recognition power and equivalence problems, which are topics in formal languages and automata theory (cs.LO) and data structures (cs.DS).
